ğŸ”¥ Setting Up Kubernetes Autoscaling (HPA) and Ingress for Your Application

To make your Jenkins Demo App more scalable and accessible via a domain, we will configure:

âœ… Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA): Auto-scales pods based on CPU usage.
âœ… Ingress Controller: Routes external traffic using a domain name instead of IP.
1ï¸âƒ£ Setting Up Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA)
ğŸ“Œ What is HPA?

    HPA (Horizontal Pod Autoscaler) dynamically scales pods based on CPU utilization.
    It ensures high availability and better performance.

ğŸš€ Step 1: Enable Metrics Server

HPA requires a Metrics Server to get CPU and memory usage. If you havenâ€™t installed it, run:

kubectl apply -f https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/metrics-server/releases/latest/download/components.yaml

Verify installation:

kubectl get deployment metrics-server -n kube-system

If it says Running, proceed to the next step.
ğŸš€ Step 2: Add Resource Limits to Backend Deployment

Modify backend deployment (backend-deployment.yaml):

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: backend
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: backend
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: backend
        image: your-dockerhub-username/jenkins-demo-backend:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: "250m"
            memory: "512Mi"
          limits:
            cpu: "500m"
            memory: "1Gi"

Apply changes:

kubectl apply -f backend-deployment.yaml

ğŸš€ Step 3: Deploy HPA

Create hpa.yaml:

apiVersion: autoscaling/v2
kind: HorizontalPodAutoscaler
metadata:
  name: backend-hpa
spec:
  scaleTargetRef:
    apiVersion: apps/v1
    kind: Deployment
    name: backend
  minReplicas: 2
  maxReplicas: 5
  metrics:
  - type: Resource
    resource:
      name: cpu
      target:
        type: Utilization
        averageUtilization: 50

Apply:

kubectl apply -f hpa.yaml

Check HPA status:

kubectl get hpa

ğŸ“ How it Works?

    If CPU usage > 50%, new pods are added (max 5 pods).
    If CPU usage drops, pods are removed (min 2 pods).

2ï¸âƒ£ Setting Up Ingress for Domain Routing
ğŸ“Œ What is Ingress?

    Ingress allows access via a domain instead of an IP.
    It routes traffic to services using a reverse proxy.
    Requires an Ingress Controller (e.g., NGINX Ingress).

ğŸš€ Step 1: Install Nginx Ingress Controller

Run:

kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/main/deploy/static/provider/cloud/deploy.yaml

Verify:

kubectl get pods -n ingress-nginx

ğŸš€ Step 2: Create an Ingress Resource

Create ingress.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: jenkins-demo-ingress
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /
spec:
  ingressClassName: nginx
  rules:
  - host: demo.yourdomain.com  # Change this to your domain
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: frontend-service
            port:
              number: 80
      - path: /api
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: backend-service
            port:
              number: 5000

Apply:

kubectl apply -f ingress.yaml

ğŸš€ Step 3: Configure DNS for Custom Domain

    If using a real domain, add an A Record pointing to the Ingress Controllerâ€™s IP.
    Get the IP:

kubectl get svc -n ingress-nginx

Look for:

ingress-nginx-controller  LoadBalancer   EXTERNAL-IP   80:xxxxx

In your domain provider's DNS, add:

    Type: A
    Name: demo
    Value: EXTERNAL-IP

âœ… Final Steps

    Deploy everything:

kubectl apply -f backend-deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f frontend-deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f hpa.yaml
kubectl apply -f ingress.yaml

Check the status:

    kubectl get hpa
    kubectl get ingress

ğŸ¯ Summary

âœ… HPA automatically scales backend pods based on CPU usage.
âœ… Ingress allows access via demo.yourdomain.com.
âœ… DNS Configuration ensures the domain resolves correctly.
